caption: Excellent, and generous, Handrolls.  Unfortunately, temporarily closed, updated 24-Jan2021.

We came to this place for dinner. we heard about this restaurant from a lot of people.  Well, it was very successful. The staff welcomed us with a smile and we felt very good. The food was just great. We loved this restaurant very much and we will definitely return to this restaurant. we highly recommend this place.
Warm welcome, good food, fair price, quick service and clean. Very impress!
So good. Really fresh fish at a great price!

We sit down and ask for help to order. Terrible experience. The server speaks hardly english and more than this didn't know anything about the menu. His excuse was that the menu just changed recently and he doesn't know. We asked him to call the chef and he couldn't come, another server came and again couldn't explain. We had to leave after 15 minutes that none of them could not explain their dishes.

Food was great and very affordable filling (definitely recommended the spicy tofu/ veggie NYC/ California). The seaweed was the only disappointing part, as the rice hadn't gotten a chance to soften it yet so it was still pretty dry. Definitely not tough though as I see some reviews have said. Also i ordered three rolls and they were all served separately so I have no idea if this is the norm or what.

Great food and the chef was really helpful. But, the cashier automatically charged me a 15% gratuity without even explaining that to me first. He was really nervous when I asked him to break down the cost. It's obvious that he didn't think I was going to give a tip, so he charged me whatever he thought I should pay. What if I wanted to leave more? I usually tip 25% for a $20 lunch, especially when having good service to help me navigate the menu.  I wonder if my dark skin, curly hair and workout clothes made him think that I wasn't going to tip.

The pasta here was phenomenal. Truly enjoyed the dinner here. Ordered the Bianchi & Neri. It was cooked to perfection as it was fresh and rich with different flavors. Can't wait to try new dishes here.  Service was excellent. The waiter made sure we had a good time. Definitely coming back here again.

There isn’t any technical outdoor space but when they unfurl the doors, it’s close enough to feel safe in these crazy times. The rolls are delicious and fairly priced if you get the combo. Sushi chef is friendlier than the staff. Will be coming back again!
This place is nice and roomy, the menu was enchanting and the prices were very inexpensive. rapidly, effective service and very personal staff members. I recommend this place.
Good sushi, reasonable prices, and a good vibe.
Fantastic hand rolls! I’ve visited countless times because of the quality of food and service.
Everything was yum and the ambience is really welcoming
epic
Really good sushi for the price
Wonderful food Amazing service We really enjoy our dinner there Definitely recommend it
It was...fine. A bit awkward to eat, and I'd like to be able to order tuna or salmon straight, rather than bathed in a sauce.
Great sushi experience! The prices are not too bad, the fish is fresh, and the staff are nice. It was more than food, but an experience.

I really like this place. Good food, nice atmosphere and friendly staff. Their Sushi is really good especially shrimp tempura, its crunchy and tasty. Nice place to hang out with friends and family. I recommend this place.

The atmosphere of the restaurant was nice. However the service staff were not so friendly. I asked if I could take pictures and did not get a clear answer. The chef brought over the waitress to ask. Still they did not answer me. They was no greeting of hello or goodbye when leaving. The hand-rolls itself were not so good. I tried the crab roll, lobster special, and the eel roll. All rolls were to sweet. Many of the rolls were marinated in mayonnaise. When I asked if the rolls should be dipped in soy sauce I did not get a clear answer. Also I asked if what were in some of the rolls, he did not know exactly what was mixed in them. I believe the service staff and staff in general should be more friendlier or greet the customers.

My go to sushi place in DMV. But do not expect regular sushi from this place. What they have is hand rolls. Always fresh ingredients and fish. Decent portion for inexpensive price. Love the atmosphere. Scallop hand roll is must try!!!
Foods are fresh, managers servers and chefs are really nice, service is awesome!!!
If you are looking for excellent sushi with a casual, clean ambience, then this is the place for you.  The hand rolls are made-to-order so you will get fresh-tasting sushi with ever bite.
Great food!
Soooo good! Love the lobster special roll with baby shrimp. Will be coming back!
Food was great, service very friendly.  Cool, contemporary vibe.

This is my second time visiting Hando medo. First time, I was thrilled to try this place. I feel like depending on the sushi chef, the taste could vary. Today it was pretty disappointing compared to last time. However overall, it is a goto sushi place in DC. By the way I am visiting from New York. Would recommend if you want to try something new in terms of sushi- instead of getting typical rolls and sashimi. Clean, good atmosphere and nice service!

The good first: Simple menu, really good sushi with perfect ratio of rice to fillings, nice decor, fun island bar type of seating, service charge automatic.  The bad: Maybe too simple on the menu, service cold and unfriendly although not terrible- the sushi roller guys were much nicer than hostess(es) and server- hopefully the guys get their fair share of tips. Could have been clearer about marking on the menu to order- wife was confused and felt like she wasn't offered a drink, while I sipped my sake. Service charge fixed- maybe would have received better more friendly service if I was free to tip accordingly. Food not available for take out. ______________________________________________ Overall Experience: So I guess this is a trendy area, lovely and all, but there are so many dining options that are great these days, specially in these trendy areas. As a former restaurant service employee, I really value authentically good service- this place absolutely did not have that. Maybe it was obvious we were visiting town. Maybe the two well- behaved kids we had with us (9 and 15) were a downer for the staff. The server looked like she was so worried about her job she couldn't even crack a smile, at all.  My son and I had gone in the night before (a Friday night) to see if we could get food to go, but nope, they don't do that, despite the fact that there were maybe 10-14 seated customers at most. Some restaurants like to make money, so we had to visit one of those. BTW, hostess, who was different than the next night's hostess, was super-unwelcoming.  With just a couple of smiles and a tiny bit of customer service skills, this place could have been 4-5 stars; given the overall experiences over two days, I would say that 2.5 stars would be accurate. I really wanted to love this place. At least the food was good.

Ok where do we start? First off I'm not one to give bad reviews. That being said this spot will get my honest opinion no matter what. 1. Sake in the wood cup tasted like hot bath water. It was sooooo bad I wondered if the cup was clean or not. 2. The cutting of sushi into six pieces didn't make it taste better. they should focus on better quality sushi then change the cups to gain better clientele for better profit.

Good for casual, inexpensive sushi. It's not temaki in a cone shape, like I am used to, it's cylindrical. All the fish appears to be chopped down, my eel had no large pieces, more of an "eel salad" sort of thing. They charge a "service fee" and say you don't need to tip, which I took a full star off for. I always leave a little extra cash for whoever was helping me. Overall, though, a good value.
Average fish, nice people... very weird presentation if u ARE A SOMEWhat traditional sashimi fan...  a little flexibility would go a long way vs  BUNCH OF WE DON’t do that’s
Great and delicious food, I loved the character the spot has, and the workers were super friendly. Will definitely eat here again.

Always a great experience and the consistency is what keeps me coming back. I go at least once a week. Arigatou!

Sushi that's quick but pretty good quality. Orders are taken and made in front of you. Don't not expect a giant menu to choose from. They have about 7 rolls they offer and they do them well. Has a small selection of beer and sake. Pretty much only Sushi, so don't expect to fill up if that's not what you're in the mood for. 4 rolls for $18 fills me up and isn't a bad deal for DC. Have been several times, will probably keep coming back.
Amazing food!
Fast service food good
A worse version of kazunori... Why would you want to have hando when you could have handy?
This is not sushi. This is hand rolls. Don’t get those mixed up. But if you’re up for some SERIOUSLY amazing hand rolls - this is where it’s at!

(Translated by Google) There are Asian-level sushi, vinegar rice is very delicious, all kinds of ingredients are also very delicious, the girl's food should be 3-4 combo full, lobster and fried shrimp taste is recommended. The waiter is very kind, and the sushi chef will watch you finish the next one, keeping the hardness and food freshness of the seaweed!!  (Original) 是有亞洲水平的壽司，醋飯非常好吃，各種配料也都很美味，以女生食量應該3-4個combo就滿飽的，lobster和炸蝦口味很推薦。服務員很親切，壽司師傅也會看你吃完才準備下一個，保持海苔的硬度與食物鮮度!!

Good sushi...but tough, uncut seaweed wrap. Maybe it's a CA thing, but we're used to bite-sized slices. That being said, I'd recommend the spicy tuna, blue crab and scallop rolls. And you can't go wrong with Japanese beer. Plus you get a "growing" towel at the end for clean-up.
Every hand roll is prepared at the bar. The fish tastes fresh. Fast service. Casual and hip atmosphere.
It was a unique experience with great service but I wouldn't go back. You shouldn't expect normal sushi all meet is minced.
I can’t believe i found a hair in my food. First and last time here
Had around 4 rolls. Such good sushi, the nori and the fish tasted quality.
Best spot in Logan Circle for a quick bite. Try the crab roll, my personal favorite.
Relaxing and good dinner spot.
Never ate there but I was asked to rate.
Very interesting sushi restaurant.  When they say the spicy tuna is spicy...believe them.  🔥🥵🔥🥵🔥

It's pronounced "Hand-o Med-o."  Very inviting decor and atmosphere.  There are 3 sushi bars, I was surprised at how large the restaurant is.  APPETIZER: Started with the Avocado appetizer for $7, wasn't thrilled with the portion size and the flavor profile.  It's basically 1/2 an avocado with some tiny shrimp.  I would skip this.  COMBO: Did the Pick 5 Combo for $22.  If I ordered them separately it would've been $30. They add 10% tax + auto 16% gratuity.  Scallop: creamy sauce, could not really tell if it was scallop Lobster Special (+shellfish): mixed with tiny shrimp and a little too creamy for me Salmon: this was by far my favorite because the salmon wasn't coated in a sauce Chef's Special: this roll changes frequently but it had great texture because of the salmon roe Smoked Salmon: mixed with cream cheese, the salmon is slightly cooked, this hand roll wasn't for me  The hand rolls came out one at a time and the nori is crispy and all the rolls were pretty tasty.  I wish the fish wasn't so coated in their sauces, sort of like salad dressing I wish you could say light, medium or heavy.  I would recommend getting the Pick 4 or Pick 5 combo and you'll leave satisfied.  BEVERAGES: Just FYI: it's the tiny glass bottles for soda 8 oz maybe for $3.  DESSERT: They don't have any yet.

I liked the quality of the fish and all of their maki is well balanced. I really really wish they'd cut my rolls when I asked for it. It would be great if you could offer to cut the rolls when the customers ask for it. I liked the overall concept of this restaurant though
Fun chef's special rolls. If you get a combo, the rolls are sent out one at a time instead of having them all made at once.
Unique sushi rolls, great atmosphere
Great place
Very tasty and reasonably priced!
Hit the spot for lunch.  The menu was confusing but worth the struggle.
Everything is delicious, but the avocado sashimi is just amazing.
Cool place... They make the hand rolls, right in front of you, one at a time. As you finish one hand roll they give you the next one. THE FISH WAS VERY FRESH AND TASTED GREAT.
This is my go to place for sushi in Washington DC. - great feel and authentic.  This is a must visit
Delicious hand rolls, filled with fresh fish and shellfish. Fast and friendly service. Loved the spicy tuna and the salmon.
Neat concept and the food was very tasty!
Too notch hand rolls and delicious sashimi! Loved the vibe.
Very good hand rolls with generous helpings of fish.
Very clean place to hang with Family and Friends. Best fresh sushi place I have ever been.

My number one pet peeve on Google reviews is when people review a place for what they want it to be instead of what it IS. This place has always served handrolls. Not classic, cold, cut sushi. If you don't like the casual atmosphere/service and made to order nature of Hando Medo, then don't eat here. The fish is insanely fresh and the prices are great for what you get.
Quick, efficient, delicious hand rolls.  But teeny-tiny. ~20$ for 4 rolls half the size of a normal roll isn't the best deal- though were 4 incredibly delicious rolls.

Food is ok not great. Service was strictly transactional and impersonal . The fish quality was mediocre at best..Were overcharged and the difficulty of getting a refund was overwhelming . For some reason they were unable to produce a receipt with cancelled transaction. Would not return.
Well-designed space and concept, good prices for the area, still working out some service/operational kinks when we went

Probably the best hand rolls I've had in the states. I had the spicy tuna, salmon, blue crab, shrimp tonkatsu, and yellowtail. They are served individually as you finish each one. Ultimate freshness. Chill atmosphere and friendly staff. 100% recommend. P.S.: They carry a couple of specialty ales from Japanese microbreweries. 😍
Excellent sushi wraps with unique twists on flavors.
Great place for hand rolls, beer & saki at a sleek modern Japanese sushi bar! Best local Thomas Circle restaurant.
One of the greatest restaurants in the city. Great personalized fresh food.
Excellent service, amazing food and really homie environment.
Enjoyable food, convenient, quick
Good food, good experience
Food is good, but the service is terrible. With all of the option on 14th, you’d think one would try harder.
Delicious and fresh sushi

Can I just say this was my favorite spot in DC   so far? Wow, the salmon was so fresh and fatty that you could see the oil on the paper! Okay, maybe that is off-putting for some folks but fatty salmon is soooo amazing. The scallop was creamy, jalapeño hamachi tasted fresh, inari was sweet and the spicy tuna was spicy and full of flavor. You're handed one hand roll at a time, that way, your seaweed is nice and crispy while the rice and other ingredients can be assembled upon finishing one right after the other. Plus, the prices are really nice for such high quality fish. Staff is really nice and I highly recommend stopping by here for Sunday lunch!
Brilliant! Minimalist deco and menu, delicious food!
Good food, good service

This place is super classy! They make your sushi rolls in front of you as you are eating which is great. There are all sorts of touches that make this place have great vibes, like the magic hand towels you dip in water and they expand, and the perfectly placed plates, personal soy sauce and ginger. The spicy tuna roll is actually really spicy! But good. The yellowtail jalapeño was also nice. The sweet potato roll was different but very tasty. I would recommend getting 3 rolls. 4 was a bit too many for most people in our party.
I like it and atmosphere is so good!! All staff is kind . Tasty is good and price is reasonable .!! Tuna and lobster are so good ! I will visit again later~ Thanks! :)
Love this quick japanese restaurant. It's a different concept that other sushi restaurants, it's hand rolls and appetizers.

I love hand rolls and these are decent but certainly not worthy of the price. The best place in the US for these in my opinion is KazuNori and based on my experience here they are certainly trying to copy the concept for DC but they miss the mark on food quality. Unfortunately I think KazuNori is only available in LA and NYC at the moment so I guess this might be the best option for the moment in DC.
Great rolls!
Quality ingredients, simple yet unique experience and process, nice environment! Excellent service and food. I will definitely continue to return here and introduce Hando Medo to more friends!!

Came in yesterday for lunch.   The atmosphere was comfortable and trendy.  I was suprised to see them make the rolls infront of me.  The young chef was knowledgable and informative and the manager took the time to show me their unique, alcohol offerings. The servers were always attentive and patient. Overall, service was amazing! Food was really good too, the rolls look so simple but pack some intricate flavors. The pictures don't really do these rolls justice. Food may not be "instagram worthy" but it definitely makes you feel like you're in Japan.  Will definitely stop by again!
Best sushi I've had in my life! The restaurant is also very clean! I don't have any pictures of my food because I ate it too fast.
Amazing experience and delicious food

Sushi always freaks me out (how could there be this much high grade raw fish in the world?) but two times here and both times I've come away impressed.  Fresh, fast and affordable - good combo by me. It's counter serve so you'll get to know your neighbor.

It's one of my favorite restaurant! Great food & great staff! You can enjoy “the real” Japanese hand rolls at this place! It’s different and unique from other Japanese restaurants. I looooove the place!
Conceptually very nice not for big groups service was accommodating, food was decent although I wouldn't go if I have an appetite portions are extremely small.
Delicious handmade, Japanese rolls (maki)!
Fair cheap sushi in a few trendy setting. For a true sushi from California, the food was disappointing...but you can't beat the price!

Don't expect to get great Sushi here. But it's definitely a great place to hang out with friends. The fish variety is acceptable considering it's more of a fast food joint than a restaurant. You can order individual maki or you can do a combo of 3, 4, 5, or 6. They also have beer and sake.
Food was delicious! Service was really great as well!
Great experience and great food

Helpful staff. Clean facility. Simple yet great menu. I tried 6 types, and all of them were great. Lobster, Scallop, and Salmon were my favorite. I definitely recommend checking this place out. Oh, and great house sake. I also did hear people raving about their spicy tea.
A sushi restaurant that has no sushi...  The hand rolls were pretty good, but the sashimi appetizer was cubed in to little pieces smothered in soy sauce and covered in parsley.

Excellent place. A fan of the concept as the food is very fresh. Personally loved the Lobster and Shellfish roll. But Hando medo isn't your usual sushi/roll place. You pick your key ingredients, and they make the roll for you. The price is fair and if you love Leechi...get the Japanese Soda!

I wanted to love this place. I really, really did. But I just wasn't impressed. Granted I am vegetarian and ate off the vegan menu only, but I felt there was very little effort put into the production and presentation of the food. I would have liked to see more creativity and bang for the buck for what I paid.
Dont do it
I loved the simplicity of the menu and the overall vibe of the place. I had 4 hand rolls, all very good except the nori was a bit chewy and made it difficult to eat. Staff was very friendly!
Incredible sushi and great service! I loved it.
Bar style seating with quick sushi and hand rolls.

For those who dislike this place needs to reevaluate their life. Seriously, this restaurant is called a HAND ROLL bar for a reason, This is what they do and they do it well. I’ve been here on numerous occasions and have never been disappointed. Their special rolls change every other day and they're all delicious. The crawfish special is my fav so far.

Love the decor and setup for ordering... feels like I’m back in Tokyo, but the service is horrible, and the food, as many other folks describe here, is not very good... plus the hand rolls aren’t actually hand rolls, just a sheet of seaweed VERY loosely rolled around stuff, so it’s unbelievably messy to eat. Miso soup was tepid temperature, green tea was from a tea bag vs real matcha... not worth going to again
The rolls are challenging to eat but tasty. The environment is pretty and service is excellent.

Hando Medo is fresh, made to order, sushi of high quality and flavor. He concept is handrolls, as in the traditional temaki form, except not rolled into a cone.  The outer nori is toasted perfectly and gives the right crunch. I had three types of temaki today after the sashimi special, Spanish mackerel with a seared skin and a ponzu sauce. The starter was super fresh and flavorful.  For the temaki, I had the hamachi, which was simply prepared with rice and hamachi, which I dipped in a little fresh wasabi and soy. The second temaki was a special, salmon and salmon roe in a spicy tuna-like sauce with a little mayo and maybe some tōgarashi. Delicious. The third was lump crab, which was lightly saladized with some mayo binder and a light citrus overtone.  Each of these items, sashimi and temaki, was prepared with care and skill. The concept of temaki is new to many in be US and can be enjoyed streetside in Tokyo and throughout Japanese cities. It’s lovely and executed perfectly at Hando Medo. Highly recommend.
Hand sushi roles, I thought were good but not great or anything.  Nice atmosphere though.

This place is terrible!   It's not a sushi restaurant like you're used to.  They only make hand rolls.  They actually roll it like a cut roll before its cut and bring it to you in their hands and put it on a paper placemat in front of you!!    I really don't want to meet who thought this was a good idea.  Seriously save yourself the disappointment and go get sushi at the grocery store, it's much better.  In addition, the service is terrible.  And that is being nice.

What a great place to enjoy some good sushi handrolls. Quick, quality, tasty, cool welcoming space. Priced fairly, especially considering tip included. My new go to spot on 14th to unwind and nourish after meetings.

Service was so fast between making the sushi and receiving it that the nori was still crispy. I loved everything I got but the best was the sweet potato roll, tempuraed sweet potato inside the roll, the sweet potato still hot, the rice warm ish, and the nori still crisp. The variations in flavor, temperature, and texture were very enjoyable.
Fun concept for a quick bite with decent sushi.
Great Japanese food place on 14th st.
Delicious hand rolls .  Great addition to DC sushi scene .  Very nice service .  Great ambience and design
I want to have a word with whomever gave this place a 4 star review.. it’s great every time. Love coming here.
Decent and friendly place. Worth a time

SO excited for some fast casual that's different and delicious. Perfect little handrolls made with warm rice and warm seaweed plus your choice of filling, plus beer or sake, etc. This ends up being a quick but satisfying meal--I think of it as the Japanese equivalent to a taco bar. It's not a meal you necessarily linger over, but it's intensely satisfying and won't break the bank. Favorites? Spicy tuna and blue crab.
delicious! awesome spot, bring some wines & liquors & i’ll live at your place:)
Best sushi I've found in DC area!
Pricey but good sushi. A good addition to 14th Street.
Had a pretty good dinner with friends! Got the standard four rolls. Pretty fun experience, but not necessarily the best sushi I’ve ever had

A pleasent surprise on the susshi experience. Great service with  sushi being prepared to get the mist most flavor out of each roll. Price point was excellent $$. Great saturday afternoon post brunch eatery. New to the 14th street corridor. Parking will be challenging.
Food was fresh and tasty.
Wow what a fantastic place. Incredibly fresh hand rolls and sashimi. I wanted to export this to my home city.

This may be my favorite sushi place I have eaten at.  Incredible atmosphere.  Chefs in the center making handrolls for you.  Know that they do not give you the rolls all at once. They roll one, give it to you to eat and time it as needed.  For those wondering, at least from my observation, they serve the sushi from lighter to darking, depending on what you have ordered.  As for the rolls, they are simple, which is sushi at its finest.  They are basically maki rolls that are not cut into pieces.  They are also not the handrolls which are conical.  Just the nori, sesame seeds, rice and the ingredient of choice.  The nori was roasted and delicious. Rice was warm, which threw me off a little but still fantastic.  Sesame seeds gave a small crunch, but I could have honestly done without it.  Fish or whatever ingredient you choose was fantastic.  Best spicy tuna I have had in a sushi place.  Not spicy mayo and tuna, it actually had heat and still tasted like tuna.  There is no tipping because they include it in the price, which I believe every restaurant should implement.  Back to basics made this one of the best sushi meals I've had in a long time.

The handrolled sushi was very good! The service was very good, attentive. The warm sake was very good as well. My favorite roll was the lobster special, followed by the breaded shrimp roll. I would come back, for sure.
Loved the ambience. Also I'm a vegetarian, and they have plenty of unique vegan sushi options. must try their radish vegan sushi!
Excellent food and service
Holy moly that blue crab roll is amazing. Great way to combine the local catch with Japanese cuisine
Serious handrolls for those already familiar with Japanese cuisine and small portions. House sake is very high quality, good Japanese beer selection. Great ambiance.
Great alternative to traditional sushi. Even the kids liked it. Friendly service too..
Music was way too loud

Fun format and lovely minimal modern interiors. The rolls are made to order and good quality which probably accounts for how expensive it is. This is close to my office so I have only been for lunch. If it were a little more affordable I would give 5 stars. Service is good and it's important to note the tip is included in the bill.

I saw the place from across the street, read the good reviews and decided to check it out. I always liked handrolls and figured it would be tasty. Good price, good quality. The handrolls aren’t traditional cone shape, cylinder instead. The seaweed is so fresh and crisp when served. Highly recommended.
Really unique handroll experience. Highly recommend!
Great service. Overall, the food was great. The tuna roll was too spicy but the salmon and yellowtail were delicious. Really great sake too.
Wow, one of the best sushi places I've been to! Would highly recommend the avocado sashimi

Amazing!! If you like sushi you MUST try Hando medo! Best hand rolls I've ever had. Great prices too. Very fresh, delicious. Only wish they had wine, not just beer and saki, but the sushi rolls, Omg the sushi rolls... The best!!

I have now tried just about everything on the menu and it is all amazing... the atmosphere is her a from the moment you walk in and the staff greats you. Attentitive service and very accommodating to our requests. Great staff and great food. Can you ask for more?

I got a salmon handroll, smoked salmon handroll, and spicy tuna handroll. They were great, be ready for the spicy tuna to actually be spicy. My only complaint is they make one roll at a time and wait til your finished until they bring you the next one. They most likely do this to keep the seaweed as crisp as possible, which I understand. I just don't like being waited on like that while I eat because I'm very slow, it's a personal preference. They're supposed to be getting a takeout option soon, so that'll be awesome.
Great hand rolls with a very courteous staff.  Quick and convenient.
Fresh food, good (and filling) maki rolls, nice people, not too expensive. Many seats available since the restaurant started only a month ago.
This place is awesome! Great service and even better sushi.
really cool place with coolest hand roll  sushi and great sake.

The sushi was really fresh and the warm sushi rice was tasty against the chilled fish and seaweed wrapper.  Add a little soy sauce and Wasabi and it was a great combination. Also, enjoyed the warm sake. Not sweet, but not too dry either.
Excellent sushi, soup, and sake! Great prices with very friendly and attentive staff.
The epitome of what the fast casual dining experience should be. The food was delicious and fresh, the staff were very friendly, and the restaurant had a great feeling/vibe.
High quality sushi in a soothing, minimalist venue. Delicious!
Not family friendly.
Great services, great hand rolls.
Yum!

From the moment you walk into the light, clean and airy bar, to the moment you exit; the warmth and pleasantness you are given(the entire staff greets welcomes you with a boisterous Japanese welcome), is the same energy that you feel walking out of the door(the entire staff heralds your exit with a “THANK YOU”). The speed, efficiency and overall experience is only matched by the tastiness of their entire menu.  Where ever you fall on the sushi-spectrum-of-enjoyment, you are guaranteed an amazing and unique dinning experience.
Upscale fresh hand roll is here🙏
Amazinginly flavorful hand rolls . .  . Very quick and personable staff. Definitely bringing my gf next time. Great addition to the Asian district of 14th st!
Great experience all around. Thier handroll is something truly special thats different from other sushi place.

Amazing experience! The uncut rolls really take you back to what sushi should be. I recommend the  Shrimp Katsu, Blue Crab (for the Old Bay lovers) and Eel. There was also a great Vegan menu for my sister. Really friendly staff and I can’t wait to come back.
Amazing, high quality rolls! Definitely recommend getting the salmon sashimi appetizer as well as the shrimp katsu hand roll.
Great new hand roll place. Lots of delicious veggie and vegan options not just seafood.
They rolls are awesome!!! Great concept. Delicious food!
